 Background                                                         71 1451     
 ----------                                                         71 1451     
                                                                    71 1451     
 This library was produced by the Low Energy Interaction Physics    71 1451     
 (LEIP) group at NC State University. The inelastic scattering      71 1451     
 thermal scattering law data for Uranium Mononitride (UN) were      71 1451     
 developed using ab initio lattice dynamics methods [1]. The        71 1451     
 LEAPR module from the NJOY code system was used to produce MF=7    71 1451     
 MT=2 and 4 for U in UN. Modifications to the LEAPR module were     71 1451     
 made to calculate the coherent elastic cross-section for UN [2].   71 1451     
 N-14 has an incoherent nuclear cross section of 0.5 barns [3];     71 1451     
 therefore, to capture both coherent and incoherent elastic         71 1451     
 scattering, the incoherent elastic TSL is tabulated in the         71 1451     
 N in UN library and the coherent elastic cross section data        71 1451     
 for UN is tabulated in U in UN library.                            71 1451     
                                                                    71 1451     
